recordings.rmk:
Gamboa, Panama, at dawn: 3-4 species singing

The recording was not modified.

The habitat was in the city of Gamboa. Keel-billed Toucans were perched in a barren tree at the side of the street. Two or three other mystery species can be heard too.

The Toucans were active and vocal in the tree. Then they flew away.

It was dawn with a mist.

"Songs and Background species IDed by Kent Livezey"

Thank you for your interest in these birds, and a big thank you to Kent!
Larry Joseph at Hazelton, BC, Canada
The same pair as in XC460021. This song series lasted about 15 minutes, most of which is presented here.
The entire song series from a pair of Keel-billed Toucans.
